description:
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MEDICAL BANK DOCTORS - Torbay Hospital&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting time to join the Bank at Torbay and South Devon NHS Foundation Trust, as it has recently become one of the first vertically-integrated health and care organisations in the country (ICO).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a highly successful organisation. In 2011 we won the Health Service Journal Acute Hospital of the Year Award and in both 2013 and 2014 we were named in the HSJ’s Top 100 Places to work. In 2015 the Trust was named as one of the 40 best-performing Trusts in England in the CHKS Top Hospital Award for 2015.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit talented, caring, professional, suitably qualified doctors to work across all grades and specialties for work ranging from a single shift to an extended post, with evening, weekend and on-call shifts available. We are keen to expand our existing team of Bank Doctors which enables you to work when it suits you. There is flexibility for you to choose your own working pattern to suit you and your life style, based on service needs and staffing requirements of the hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Specialties include Anaesthetics, Accident &amp; Emergency, General Medicine, General Surgery, Obstetrics &amp; Gynaecology, Trauma &amp; Orthopaedics, Oral &amp; Maxillo-Facial Surgery and Paediatrics to list but a few.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Being on our Bank you would get first pick of all shifts before they are offered to agencies and in return for your hard work, reliability and loyalty, Torbay and South Devon NHS Foundation Trust will offer a range of staff benefits:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive pay rates, with weekly pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assistance with clinical appraisal and revalidation support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Long and short term placements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Choice of available shifts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of working on various wards and across specialties&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Staff Restaurant and Coffee Shop&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Well resourced library and learning facilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Should you wish to discuss the opportunities on offer in more detail, or even to arrange a visit to our hospital, please do not hesitate to contact Krystyna Webber, Medical Recruitment &amp; Temporary Staffing Officer on 01803 656673 or e-mail krys.webber@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All you need to do to apply is to complete the on-line NHS Jobs application form in full.&lt;/p&gt;
